@NODE 0. "Introduction"
Introduction
~~~~~~~~~~~~
Have you ever extracted archives to the ramdisk and after you have
inspected them tried to get rid of them ? When you are using DOpus
you have selected all files and directories of the archive with the 
mouse and then deleted them using the delete button. If you are
looking at many archives on a day e.g. browsing through an Aminet or
Fish CD you know that deleting inspected extracted archives from ram: 
is a boring job, because you have to be careful not to delete other
directories like ENV or your disk.info file.

Now you got an AREXX script for DOpus which is making the job for
you. It deletes all files in the ram disk except the following files
and directories:

- Clipboards (dir)
- ENV (dir)
- T (dir)
- Disk.info


@ENDNODE

